label.value: protein complex involved in cell-cell adhesion

definition.value: Any protein complex that is capable of carrying out some part of the process of cell-cell adhesion.

label.value: protein complex involved in cell adhesion

definition.value: Any protein complex that is capable of carrying out some part of the process of cell-cell adhesion.

label.value: protein complex involved in cell-matrix adhesion

definition.value: Any protein complex that is capable of carrying out some part of the process of cell-matrix adhesion.

label.value: laminin binding involved in cell-matrix adhesion

definition.value: Any laminin protein binding that occurs as part of cell-matrix adhesion.

label.value: collagen binding involved in cell-matrix adhesion

definition.value: Any collagen binding that occurs as part of cell-matrix adhesion.

label.value: integrin binding involved in cell-matrix adhesion

definition.value: Any integrin binding that occurs as part of the process of cell-matrix adhesion.

label.value: cadherin binding involved in cell-cell adhesion

definition.value: Any cadherin binding that occurs as part of the process of cell-cell adhesion.
A collagen trimer that forms networks.
A supramolecular assembly of fibrillar collagen complexes in the form of a long fiber (fibril) with transverse striations (bands).
A complex of collagen trimers such as a fibril or collagen network.
A protein complex that consists of collagen triple helices associated to form a network.
A protein complex that consists of collagen triple helices associated to form a sheet-like network.
A supramolecular assembly of collagen trimers with a 'beads on a string'-like structure.
A specialised collagen fibril that functions as an anchor, binding to other collagen structures.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a peptidyl-proline 4-dioxygenase.
Any collagen timer that is part of a basement membrane.
An antiparallel dimer of two collagen VII trimers, one end of which is embedded in the lamina densa while the other end attaches to banded collagen fibrils in the dermis.
A protein complex that includes Mis16(Yippee family) and|or Mis18 (WD repeat) subunits that is involved in the deposition of centromere specific (CENP-A containing) nucleosomes at the centromere.

label.value: transmembrane transporter activity involved in import into cell

definition.value: Any transmembrane transporter activity that is involved in importing some substance into a cell.
Any subdivision of a chromosome along its length.
Division of a stem cell during which it retains its identity and buds off a daughter cell with a new identity.
A myofibril of a skeletal muscle fiber.

Symmetric division of a stem cell to produce two stem cells of the same type as the parent. Symmetric stem cell division is necessary for amplification of stem cell populations in the absence of sources of stem cells external to an existing population.
Cell division in which both daughter cells are of the same type.

label.value: symmetric division of skeletal muscle satellite stem cell

definition.value: The symmetric division of a skeletal muscle satellite stem cell, resulting in two skeletal muscle satellite stem cells.  This process is involved in amplification of the pool of these cells.
The self-renewing division of a germline stem cell, to produce a daughter stem cell and a daughter germ cell which will divide to form one or more gametes.
Division of a germline stem cell to produce two germline stem cells of the same type as the parent.

label.value: male germline stem cell symmetric division

definition.value: The symmetric division of a male germline stem cell to produce two male germline stem cells.  An example of this is found in mammalian spermatogonial stem cells, some proportion of which divide symmetrically, so amplifying the population. The choice between asymmetric and symmetric division in this case appears to be internal and stochastic.
Any protein complex that is part of or has some part in a hemidesmosome.
Increases the activity of 1-phosphatidylinositol 4-kinase.
A protein complex consisting of a Dcp1 regulatory subunit and a Dcp2 catalytic subunit that has mRNA cap binding activity and is involved in decapping of nuclear-transcribed mRNA.
The binding activity of a molecule that brings together two or more protein molecules, or a protein and another macromolecule or complex as a key step in receptor mediated endocytosis.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a FXYD domain.

label.value: integral component of the cytoplasmic side of the plasma membrane

definition.value: The component of the plasma membrane consisting of the gene products that penetrate only the cytoplasmic side of the membrane.

label.value: anchored component of the cytoplasmic side of the plasma membrane

definition.value: The component of the plasma membrane consisting of gene products and protein complexes with covalently attached hyrdophobic anchors products that penetrate only the cytoplasmic side of the membrane.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any member of the Tissue inhibitors of metalloproteinases (TIMPs) family. TIMPs are endogenous protein regulators of the matrix metalloproteinase (MMPs) family

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any member of the FBXO protein family. Members of this family have an F-box protein motif of approximately 50 amino acids that functions as a site of protein-protein interaction.

label.value: positive regulation of G1|S transition of mitotic cell cycle

definition.value: Any cell cycle regulatory process that promotes the commitment of a cell from G1 to S phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: regulation of DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity.

label.value: negative regulation of DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity.

label.value: positive regulation of DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity.

label.value: regulation of meiosis by regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: A regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter that results in regulation of meiosis.

label.value: regulation of cytokinetic cell separation by regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: A regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter that results in regulation of cytokinetic cell separation.

label.value: regulation of cytokinesis by regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: A regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter that results in regulation of cytokinesis.

label.value: positive regulation of meiosis by negative regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of meiosis by stopping, preventing, or reducing the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: positive regulation of meiosis by positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of meiosis by activating or increasing the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: negative regulation of G1|S transition of mitotic cell cycle by negative regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of G1|S transition of mitotic cell cycle by stopping, preventing, or reducing the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: regulation of nucleus size involved in G1 to G0 transition

definition.value: Any regulation of nucleus size that is involved in G1 to G0 transition.

label.value: regulation of cell shape involved in G1 to G0 transition

definition.value: Any regulation of cell shape that is involved in G1 to G0 transition.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an oligopeptide.
